articles.description: Ivy Smith Jr. had 22 points and seven rebounds on Monday night to help Grambling beat Texas Southern 78-55 for its 10th straight win.
articles.headline: Grambling wins 10th straight, beats Texas Southern 78-55

articles.description: Teddy Allen scored 16 points, giving No. 20 West Virginia a needed spark off the bench in an 82-66 victory over TCU on Monday night.
articles.headline: Strong bench scoring helps No. 20 WVU beat TCU 82-66

images.caption: Sagaba Konate and Esa Ahmad come up with back-to-back blocks on TCU.
images.name: West Virginia brings TCU the stuffing

articles.description: When Kimbal Mackenzie gives the Bison a dramatic 65-64 victory with a buzzer-beating 3, announcer Doug Birdsong provides a rather energetic call to match the enthusiasm of the fans rushing the court.
articles.headline: Bucknell announcer goes crazy after buzzer-beater

images.caption: When Kimbal Mackenzie gives the Bison a dramatic 65-64 victory with a buzzer-beating 3, announcer Doug Birdsong provides a rather energetic call to match the enthusiasm of the fans rushing the court.
images.name: Bucknell announcer goes crazy after buzzer-beater

articles.description: Ross Cummings hit four 3-pointers and finished with 21 points and Jordan Strawberry had 18 points, six rebounds, seven assists and two steals to help Mercer beat Samford 74-69 on Monday night.
articles.headline: Cummings hits 4 3s, scores 21; Mercer beats Samford 74-69

articles.description: Javaris Jenkins scored 21 points, made 4 of 6 from 3-point range and blocked three shots Monday night to help Savannah State beat North Carolina A&T 108-106.
articles.headline: Savannah State beats NC A&T in MEAC showdown

articles.description: The Bison are down eight with under 30 seconds remaining, but get a couple of buckets before Kimbal Mackenzie hits a 3-pointer as time expires to beat the Raiders 65-64.
articles.headline: Bucknell uses incredible comeback, buzzer-beater to top Colgate
